product_ranges.title: Apply yourself. Print. - Red

global-fap.description:
No. 451 / Apply yourself.

What do you need to feel strong? What would it take for you to be complete? Can you heal the wounds of the past within you? What would it take for you to believe that your dreams are within your grasp? When will you recognize how much originality, potential, and power exists inside you, and waits impatiently for you to use it? When will you see that the love, effort, and respect you show yourself is the source of that which you show others? Don’t you know that by investing in yourself you are improving the world?

product_ranges.title: Stop and reflect. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 453 / Stop and reflect.

The evil you perceive in others exists within you as well, and it always will. The people you disagree with most are the most important for you to understand. Don’t forget how often you’ve been wrong. Don’t forget that they disagree with you too. They represent a piece of humanity which you lack, and connecting with them can only make you more whole. If you aren’t strong enough to take in what is worst in the world and transform it into what is best in you, then you will try to destroy it, and inevitably destroy yourself.

product_ranges.title: Nothing is perfect. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 454 / Nothing is perfect.

Tragedy and splendor intermingle in every moment, and touch every heart. The terrible and the sublime are woven into the fabric of our existence with precisely the same skill and eloquence. Struggle, loss, and pain run through one life and into the next, but, just like love and compassion, they connect us. A grand, vast, incomprehensible pattern would be unravelled without them. And though your life is itself only a single thread in that tapestry, the beauty of humanity would be that much less intricate without you.

product_ranges.title: Strive for excellence. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 455 / Strive for excellence.

You’ll never achieve it. Your desire for it will never be fulfilled. It’s beyond you. If you’re foolish enough to dream of it, if you’re crazy enough to pursue it in earnest, you’ll sacrifice everything and suffer greatly. Oh, how the best in you will ache and burn to give away. But, when you’ve finally found your limit, which will be so far from your impossible goal, when you can go no further and there’s nothing left, you’ll know, at last, without doubt or regret, that nothing is so worth years of pain as a single moment of glory.

product_ranges.title: Don’t be dIscouraged. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 456 / Don’t be discouraged.

Your daily struggle doesn’t exist on the condition of being validated. You’ve made it this far, and that counts. But this is not the destination. This is not your arrival. This is the plateau. This is the chance to climb higher. This is the decisive moment. Nothing stands between you and what you want but opportunity and hesitation. You haven’t been called to conquer the world, only your doubt. Stop questioning, start preparing. Find your way up. Forget happiness, pursue strength.

product_ranges.title: Make your dreams come true. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 457 / Make your dreams come true.

The path between can’t and can isn’t hidden. It’s the breadth of your resilience, the depth of your conviction, the height of your character. It’s not in the stars or in the cards. It’s not in the graces of the powerful, nor in the cheers of the crowd. It’s not a thing to be obtained, but one to be called forth. It’s within you. It’s your spirit. It’s your very fiber. It’s in you now, just as it’s always been. You only need to believe. Your power far exceeds your limits. Will it into being. Right now. Why do you hesitate?

product_ranges.title: Take charge of your life. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 458 / Take charge of your life.

Where is your dream? How far is it? Fight for it. Sacrifice for it. Seek it amidst the doubt, seek it amidst the discouragement. If it were easy to achieve, it wouldn’t be called a dream. The harder it is to reach, the stronger you’ll grow in its pursuit. What is growth but the struggle toward the light? The bigger you become, the smaller you used to be. Persevere. Persist. Be single minded. Be undaunted. Be invulnerable to distraction. Be whatever your dream demands of you. Accept that gift. Be transformed.

global-fap.description:
No. 459 / You can do anything.

Where but in the grip of fear should you summon courage? Where but at your lowest point should you be looking up? Where but in adversity should you acquire fortitude? Where but at the point of being lost should you find the way? Where but beneath the heaviest burden should you gather up your strength? Where but in your downfall should you hope to be redeemed? Where but in the din of lies should you speak the truth? Where else but in the darkness should you carry the light?

product_ranges.title: Rise to the challenge. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 460 / Rise to the challenge.

When you’re pushed down, you must stand. When you’re completely surrounded, you must stand. When you’re the only one left standing, you must stand. You must stand because you are able. Because you are aware. Because you know what’s worth standing for. Because life is a struggle, and to face it, to face the truth, to face yourself, is to accept that struggle with pride and dignity. Because the struggle to stand, for those who choose to live, is far less terrible than the struggle to live for those who are afraid to stand.

product_ranges.title: Reach higher. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 461 / Reach higher.

With kindness you discover love. With love you grow strength. With strength you earn freedom. With freedom you experience consequence. With consequence you learn responsibility. With responsibility you seek wisdom. With wisdom you use patience. With patience you value kindness. The greatest is found among the least. The everlasting is revealed in the evanescent. The journey’s end is the return home. Transcendence is half in the reaching up and half in the letting go.

product_ranges.title: Courage counts. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 463 / Courage counts.

It takes much more than courage to finish, but it’s all you need to begin. Those with the courage to accept past failings are the stewards of future prosperity. Those with the courage to uphold their principles in the face of horror are the bearers of truth. The greatest necessities will come with the greatest demands. Courage can be as unpleasant as fear, and it’s only useful when it’s least desirable. The difficulty isn’t finding courage, but embracing it and holding on.

global-fap.description:
No. 464 / Don’t worry about what people think of you.

Your success isn’t the reason they’ve failed. Your strength hasn’t caused them to be weak. Your confidence isn’t the source of their insecurity. Your values haven’t led to their misguidance. Your growth isn’t the catalyst for their decay. Your wellbeing shouldn’t warrant their jealousy. Your resolve doesn’t validate their anger. Your fulfillment isn’t why they feel empty. Be honest and you’ll be respected. Be kind and you’ll be loved. Be yourself and you’ll be able to see others as they truly are.

product_ranges.title: You’ve come a long way. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 465 / You’ve come a long way.

When you look back on your path through life, it’s not many stumbling steps that you’ll recall, but one great journey. Not consecutive defeats, but cumulative victory. Not that you were often lost, but that you always found your way. You won’t see time wasted, but lessons learned. Not the pain, but the wisdom. Not the loss, but the recovery. Not the droughts or the floods, but the rhythm of seasons. You won’t see the struggle, but its meaning: that you are better now than you were before. And that’s all that matters.

product_ranges.title: Do your own thing. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 468 / Do your own thing.

Are they looking down on you, or is their world upside down? The status quo that you defy is the limit to their creativity. The convention that you challenge is what they rely on for stability. The rule that you ignore is the line they are too afraid to cross. When you stand on your own, they see that they’re leaning on someone else. When you speak for yourself, they see they’re all saying the same thing. When you carve your own path, they see they don’t know where they’re going. What makes you distinct won't always make you popular.

product_ranges.title: Your flaws make you unique. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 469 / Your flaws make you unique.

Every flaw is balanced by a grace. The one you choose to dwell on comes to define you. To be beautiful is to be blemished in the perfect way, and beauty is elevating. To stoke the inner fire is to be consumed, but others are warmed. To love is to hurt, but also to heal. To live at all is to suffer, to strain, to always be aware of the inevitable end of living; but life is beautiful, and warm, and it offers the chance to love. So can you bear the worst of it and celebrate the best?

global-fap.description:
No. 470 / Stick with it.

If they say it can’t be done, imagine what they’ll say once you’ve done it. If they say you shouldn’t go too far, imagine what they’ll say when you’ve gone all the way. If they say you’re going to cause trouble, imagine what they’ll say when you’ve effected change. No one bars a door unless there’s treasure on the other side. No one guards the road unless it leads to freedom. No one tries to hold you back unless your progress is a threat. Don’t ignore your dissenters, let them be your guide.

If they say you’re going to cause trouble, imagine what they’ll say when you’ve effected change. No one bars a door unless there’s treasure on the other side. No one guards the road unless it leads to freedom. No one tries to hold you back unless your progress is a threat. Don’t ignore your dissenters, let them be your guide.

product_ranges.title: Don’t get complacent. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 471 / Don’t get complacent.

As soon as you carve your own path, others will begin paving over it. Your innovation is the future decline. Your establishment is someone else’s conquest. Your follower will someday lead. If you’ve set the status quo, prepare to be challenged. If you’ve become conventional, prepare to be disrupted. If you’ve written a rule, prepare to be ignored. Yesterday and tomorrow are not so distant as they may seem, get as far as you can today. Travel lightly. Don’t look back. Obsolescence is catching up.

product_ranges.title: You can’t fake it. Print. - Black

It’s hard to describe. It’s easy to see. It stirs your soul. It stills your mind. It moves your ass. It’s immediately recognizable. It’s impossible to define. It’s unmistakable energy. It’s irresistible attraction. It’s captivating. It’s liberating. It keeps you grounded. It carries you away. It defines who you are. It changes what you appear to be. It leads you to the center of your being. It loses you within yourself. It asks so little of you. It tells you everything you need to know. But it has to be real. It has to be you.

global-fap.description:
No. 473 / Treat others as you want to be treated.

Behind those folded arms, a heart needs love. Behind that furrowed brow, a mind needs to understand. Behind that ego, one soul needs all others. The bond can’t be broken. All your twisting only tangles us further. All your pulling only draws us closer. Both vengeance and passion only bring us closer. To collide or embrace, we only come closer. In contest or cooperation, we’re always coming closer. To know the other is to know yourself, and what a terrible burden that knowing is. No wonder you want to look away.

Though you choose between difficulty and defeat, never deny that you have a choice. Don’t just follow your heart, but steer it.

product_ranges.title: Keep trying. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 475 / Keep trying.

You’ll never know where your true limits are unless you go and find them. While you may never actually touch the white-hot mass of burning pain that is the true end of your ability, you can get much closer than you think. And when you inevitably fail, you’ll learn that failure isn’t the end. You’ll still be intact. The world will still be intact. It’s always changing, and so are you. And that’s what allows you to try again. If it were easy to achieve, it wouldn’t be a dream.

If the future you hope to cast is to come out whole, don’t fear the flames, but stoke them higher. This is the transformation you seek. This is the answer to your prayer. This is what opportunity feels like. You have paid the price, now you must extract the value.

product_ranges.title: Be tough. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 477 / Be tough.

Just at the shadowy edges of your preparation, the shuddering blow is waiting to fall. The worst of it comes when you’re hurt and tired, when technique and conditioning can do no more. The real test won’t prove what you’re ready for, but what you’re made of. When it comes, your core will be split and unravelled, fibrous and knotted though it may be. You’ll be naked, broken, and alone. When the real test comes, there will be nothing left of you… except two words ringing defiantly through hollow doubt: I can!

product_ranges.title: Be kind to yourself. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 478 / Be kind to yourself.

You are the inmate and the guard of the prison in which you are confined. You are the walls, and the bars, and the prison itself. You are the warden. You are the judge. You are the authority. You are the law of fear, inhibition, and self-doubt. But you are the liberator also. You are the light of hope. You are the redeeming power of courage, resilience, and conviction. You are the second chance (and the third and fourth). You are the hand that holds the key. When will you grant yourself the freedom that you deserve?

global-fap.description:
No. 479 / Your potential is unlimited.

Don’t deny us your contributions. Don’t deprive us of the adventure of exploring your depths, or the thrill of unraveling your story. Create. Though your creation will be imperfect—as you are imperfect, as we are all imperfect—create. From your imperfections, the power of the unpredictable and the beauty of the unknown arise. Life arises. Life begins in darkness, in mystery, in hidden places, but, through you, life strives eternally to touch the outer world and be transformed in its light.

Follow your passion and you won’t be led astray. Accept nothing but your best, and always look for the best in others. Acknowledge your flaws, but never believe that you’re irredeemable. Own your past mistakes, but always strive to avoid them in the future. Be objective in all things. Even an unpleasant truth is liberating, even blissful ignorance is a prison. Be formidable. Be so hard to beat that they’ll regret winning. Shine so brightly that everything your light touches will be transformed by your brilliance.

product_ranges.title: Stop wasting your time. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 481 / Stop wasting your time.

Time consumes everything, and gives you such a small piece of itself. And, in the end, it keeps that too. How far away is your dream? How long will it take to get there? Time is passing. While you play, while you wait, while you complain, while you regret, while you pretend it doesn’t exist, time is passing. This moment is already gone. What will you do with those that remain? Time consumes another day. How did you spend it? A lifetime slips between your fingers. Will you grasp it?

global-fap.description:
No. 482 / See the best in yourself.

Just as malice runs through every heart, the struggle of life runs through every experience. The unsavory must be sifted out from the wholesome. The pith must be pulled away from the fruit. Tragedy must first be endured before glory is achieved. From many small horrors, the grand beauty of this world is woven. You are far more than the sum of your mistakes. Though you belong to humanity, you are the proprietor of your soul. It’s what you’re capable of in spite of your flaws that makes you wonderful.

product_ranges.title: You are worthy of love. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 483 / You are worthy of love.

Beauty isn’t created, but discovered. At our best we are only able to reveal it to the world. Beauty extends far past the narrow limits of any single lifetime, and well outside the grasp of our power to comprehend. We don’t control beauty, we are beggars at its feet. It is beyond us. It is greater than us. It runs through us, we are made of it. We are such a small part of the beauty of life, and the part of it we are able to see is even smaller. It’s no wonder, then, that we so rarely see it in ourselves.

product_ranges.title: You have to do it for yourself. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 484 / You have to do it for yourself.

The meaning of your life is yours alone to create. No one else can make you happy. No one else can fill you up. No one else can fight your battle or take your journey. When you’re at the bottom, looking up can be discouraging. It’s such a long way. But every strained pull makes you stronger. Every painful hold makes you tougher. Every inch you rise makes you more determined not to fall. Have you slid back? Have you been knocked down? Have you ever really even had the courage to climb?

product_ranges.title: Have some fortitude. Print. - Black

global-fap.description:
No. 487 / Have some fortitude.

You’re going to get your ass kicked whether you’re afraid or not, so don’t waste time being afraid. Hide from your problems and you’ll just be confined with them. Run from your obligations and you’ll just exhaust yourself before they catch up. Deny the call and it’ll just haunt you after the opportunity has passed. The real danger isn’t revealed by imagination, it’s hidden in shadow. You can’t see it. You can’t avoid it. The best you can do is prepare yourself to face it. Grow strong. Get fast. Build support. You can win.

global-fap.description:
No. 488 / Own your future.

Though you’re only a small part of the world, it’s incomplete without you. Though it moves you, you’re also moving it. We’re not separate lives, but one big life. We’re not divergent streams, but eddies in a single river. Even against our will, the current of time urges us forward. Even in disharmony, we move in the same direction. Even when we’re lost, we’re not without a destination. But you set the course of your life by your will. So pay attention to where you’re going, because you’re pulling us along with you.
